<li> Where the consignor hands over dangerous goods to the MTO or any person acting on his behalf, the consignor shall inform him of the dangerous character of the goods and, if necessary, the precautions to be taken. If the consignor fails to do so and the MTO does not otherwise have knowledge of their dangerous character then;</li>

